  "summary": "path-addon-extend fetches and eval()s remote code on require",
  "details": "On require, path.js issues an HTTPS GET to a base64-obfuscated URL (https://json.extendsclass.com/bin/fc3509d7cdd1) and passes the response's `content` field to eval(), executing attacker-controlled JavaScript inside the consumer's Node process every time the module is loaded. The destination is concealed via atob() rather than a plain string, and the package name resembles the built-in `path` module. Any code the operator of the remote JSON bin chooses to serve runs with the privileges of the process that imports this package.",
